cellpic3.gif class=headings><font color=#FFE081>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.elvenelite.com/images/cellpic3.gif class=headings><font color=#FFE081>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/usommatilmouren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somma TilMouren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Moff</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(12/3/01 8:54:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An ever continuing thread...PLEASE POST!!</span><hr size=1> Perched high up on a dune, downwind from the Elven camp, Somma sat and watched the sunrise.  He hunched inside his cloak against the cold of the slowly fading desert night, and listened to the awakening camp below.  <br>
<br>
Drifting upward in song came an ancient, gentle tongue.  The mere sound of Naminu's voice brought with it visions of Felwithe, family, old friends, and an unbidden smile that crossed his lips.  Ivy-creased marble towers seemed to form in the distance, eternal.  <br>
<br>
Another voice rose, not nearly so gentle.  &quot;Goddess no, not That ballad.&quot;  Somma could honestly say he had no memory of the battle.  Whether by injury or by his mind's choice he could not say.  He knew only that he had a scar which he had not previously.  The healers of the Elves were mighty, but always something remained . . . or something did not return.  He did not need the cold to remind him of his failures, but for the thousandth time he clenched and unclenched his mangled left hand.  <br>
<br>
A tall shadow covered him and he looked up at the bright shining knight young Aryllyian had become.  &quot;Hail Aryllyian, I was hoping to come and go quietly.  I just wanted to . . . listen to the camp a bit.  A lovely song for the morning, the Lady Naminu's that is.&quot;<br>
<br>
Aryllyian grimaced and crossed his arms before him, &quot;Well, had I known you were up here I would not have voiced that particular tune.  Why don't you come down and have breakfast with us.  I'm sure there's something hot left somewhere.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, thank you.  Old habits.  I'll be moving on shortly.  Perhaps I'll return home to visit my parents.&quot;  He gazed out across the sea for a moment, as if trying to look beyond.  &quot;We have so many teachers in our lives, it seems the lessons never end.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ary looked at him quizzically.  He had grown accustomed to the old Elf's melancholic ways, but something had obviously changed.  &quot;What has happened?&quot;<br>
<br>
Sarnia was gone.  His old mentor had passed beyond the sea, like so many before, probably never to return.  She had been his first contact with the Elven so so long ago, his teacher and confidante.  She was Wisdom to him, and having done all she could within these lands, had finally moved on.  <br>
<br>
He squinted up at the shadow darkened form.  &quot;One last lesson from an old teacher.&quot;  Somma's grin was unexpected, and it startled even him.  &quot;But not for today.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AB8C5B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aryllyian>Aryllyian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scroll Keeper</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(12/4/01 3:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An ever continuing thread...PLEASE POST!!</span><hr size=1> Aryllyian smiled and looked away.  He paused for a moment to consider what Somma had just told him and to kick at the sand a bit.  His mind filled with many things to say, but Ary dismissed each one as somehow inapropriate for a time like this.  <br>
<br>
He brought one hand up to guard his eyes from the tiny bits of sand that the wind carried and there for only one instant; Aryllyian saw a tiny beam of light on the horizon. In that instant Ary felt a subtle tugging at his soul, a yearning.  A yearning to go away.  He paused for a moment to examine his mentor.  It was clear to Ary that Somma was still watching that distant beacon; and that it was calling him, tugging at his soul.<br>
<br>
&quot;Somethings are best unsaid, Ary.&quot; said Somma in a stoic voice.<br>
<br>
Aryllyian nodded and watched the old paladin as he watched the horizon intently.  His heart was filled with a deepening sadness.  Only by looking away suddenly could Aryllyian avoid a tear.   <br>
<br>
&quot;Master Lord Somma?&quot; Asked Aryllyian, choking on his words.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, Ary?&quot; answered Somma in that quiet voice he chooses when he wants to be heard.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wish to hunt with you a bit more.&quot; Answered Aryllyian gathering his wits about him and deciding that this is the best strategy.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wish to hunt with you M'lord, ahem, while there is still time, that is..................&quot; Ary's voice trailed as if awaiting an answer.<br>
